# Walkthrough: V5 Institutional Hardening

This walkthrough demonstrates the restoration of the Metadata Action Bar and the high-fidelity Settings Drawer, with strict visibility guards for the empty state.

## 1. Metadata Action Bar (Hub)
The "Purple Era" Action Bar has been restored. It provides a dense, forensic summary of the current ledger state.

- **Forensic Stats**: Shows total Accounts, transactions in flight, and system mode.
- **Global REF# Input**: Compact text input for rapid reference labeling.
- **Analytics & Settings Gear**: Quick access to deep diagnostics and grid controls.

![Metadata Hub Reference](file:///C:/Users/asmia/.gemini/antigravity/brain/410a76b2-0025-4cfc-a894-2bba5b8c33e5/uploaded_media_1770145350861.png)
> [!NOTE]
> The image above shows the Hub. I have since updated the logic so it **only** appears once data is present, as per your instruction.

## 2. High-Fidelity Settings Drawer
The drawer is now a multi-tabbed interactive panel.
- **System**: Features the **Focus Lens** (Workspace Dexterity) and Theme selection (Rainbow, Wave Blue, etc.).
- **Columns**: Logic to toggle Tabulator visibility for every field (Date, Ref#, Debit, etc.).
- **Preferences**: Controls for REF overrides and Tax Calculation math.

## 3. Empty State Hardening
The UI has been hardened to ensure a clean first impression.
- **Conditional Rendering**: The Metadata Hub and Account Switcher are wrapped in a `hasData` guard. They will only manifest once your forensic documents are parsed and the grid is initialized.
- **"Waiting" Header**: The header card displays a clean "WAITING TO GET STARTED" animation until ingestion begins.

## 4. Forensic Console Trace
You can audit the entire browser-side state by running `window.getSettingsTrace()` in your console. This provides a 1:1 view of the institutional registry variables.
